# Mermaid For Visuals

- Use Mermaid for every visual artifact (flows, sequences, architecture, state, timeline, dependency, and process diagrams).
- Prefer Mermaid code blocks in Markdown docs and AI responses instead of image-based diagrams.
- Keep diagrams concise, readable, and directly tied to current implementation details.
- When a visual is requested, provide Mermaid first; use plain text only when user explicitly asks for no diagrams.

## Example

```mermaid
flowchart LR
  Jira[Jira Sprint Data] --> API[API Gateway]
  API --> Lambda[Lambda Summarize Function]
  Lambda --> Bedrock[Amazon Bedrock]
  Bedrock --> Lambda
  Lambda --> API
```
